      • addCommandModifier

        <T> CommandPropertiesManager addCommandModifier(java.lang.Class<T> propertyType,
                                                java.util.function.BiConsumer<T,CommandHandleBuilder> configurator)
        The provided configurator is used to modify commands that possess the specified property. This behavior is added onto any existing behavior. When a command is registered with that property (usually an annotation), the provided configurator is applied. If there are already commands registered, the configurator is applied to those as well.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the propertyType
        Parameters:
        propertyType - the class of the property
        configurator - a BiConsumer. The first argument is the property. The second argument is the CommandHandleBuilder the property is attached to.

        Returns:

      • addParameterModifier

        <T> CommandPropertiesManager addParameterModifier(java.lang.Class<T> propertyType,
                                                  java.util.function.BiConsumer<T,CommandParameterBuilder> configurator)
        The provided configurator is used to modify commands that possess the specified property. This behavior is added onto any existing behavior. When a parameter of the provided propertyType is found, the provided configurator is applied. If there are already parameters of that type registered, the configurator is applied to those as well.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the propertyType
        Parameters:
        propertyType - the class of the property
        configurator - a BiConsumer. The first argument is the property. The second argument is the CommandHandleBuilder the property is attached to.
